  "prompt": "What is the best massage oil blend for massage quality, feel, popularity among therapists, and skin? (example Grapeseed 75%, Apricot 15%, Jojoba 10%)",
  "response": "Creating a high-quality massage oil blend that is popular among therapists and beneficial for the skin involves selecting oils that offer various therapeutic properties, good slip for massage, and are well-absorbed without leaving a greasy residue. Here\u2019s a well-balanced and popular blend that meets these criteria:\n\n**Massage Oil Blend:**\n- **Grapeseed Oil: 60%**\n- **Sweet Almond Oil: 20%**\n- **Jojoba Oil: 10%**\n- **Avocado Oil: 10%**\n\n**Properties and Benefits:**\n\n1. **Grapeseed Oil (60%)**:\n   - Light texture, non-greasy, easily absorbed by the skin\n   - Rich in antioxidants and vitamin E\n   - Suitable for most skin types\n   - Excellent for creating a smooth massage experience\n\n2. **Sweet Almond Oil (20%)**:\n   - Medium-light texture, good slip for massage\n   - Rich in vitamins A, E, and fatty acids\n   - Nourishing and hydrating for the skin\n   - Known to be hypoallergenic and suitable for sensitive skin\n\n3. **Jojoba Oil (10%)**:\n   - Closely resembles the skin\u2019s natural sebum\n   - Highly stable and non-comedogenic\n   - Moisturizing without clogging pores\n   - Contains vitamins E and B\n\n4. **Avocado Oil (10%)**:\n   - Rich and nourishing texture\n   - Packed with vitamins A, D, and E\n   - Beneficial for dry or mature skin\n   - Enhances skin's elasticity\n\n**Optional Additions:**\n\nYou can customize this blend by adding essential oils for aromatherapy benefits. Popular choices include:\n\n- **Lavender Essential Oil**: Relaxing and soothing\n- **Peppermint Essential Oil**: Refreshing and invigorating\n- **Eucalyptus Essential Oil**: Revitalizing and clear-headed\n\n**Instructions:**\n\n1. Mix the carrier oils (Grapeseed, Sweet Almond, Jojoba, and Avocado) in a clean, dry bottle.\n2. For every 100 ml of your base oil blend, add approximately 10-20 drops of essential oils (test the ratio according to personal preference).\n3. Shake well before each use to ensure all oils are well blended.\n\n**Conclusion:**\n\nThis blend combines the light texture and therapeutic properties of multiple oils, ensuring a pleasant massage experience while nourishing and moisturizing the skin. It is favored among therapists for its versatility and ability to cater to various skin types.",
